flowchart LR

  subgraph CLAIM["1. Single architecture claim"]
    C1["A now supports one clear claim"]
    C2["The current wired platform is a real, bounded, intentional, materially seated full-lifecycle system whose major truth boundaries are explicit, owned, and governable"]
    C3["It is not just a set of cloud services or a project diagram"]
    C4["It is a managed-first platform with explicit phase closure, explicit evidence, and explicit runtime and evidence roots across spine, learning and evolution, and operational closure under one run and process contract"]
  end

  subgraph OBJECT["2. Object of A and boundary with Bi"]
    O1["The object of this claim is the current wired platform as it exists now"]
    O2["Target posture, repin history, and later hardening or proof history explain why the wired object has this shape, but they are not the primary object of A"]
    O3["A is not the same as production-readiness"]
    O4["A proves the architecture and ownership are real; it does not yet claim that every boundary has been pressure-proven at the intended production envelope"]
  end

  subgraph CHAIN["3. End-to-end lifecycle chain"]
    L1["Run legitimacy and source legitimacy"]
    L2["Canonical behavioural traffic becomes governed runtime entry truth"]
    L3["Real-time decision truth is built through explicit RTDL boundaries"]
    L4["Runtime behavior becomes durable audit and archive truth"]
    L5["Some of that truth becomes operational case truth and authoritative label truth"]
    L6["Archive plus label truth becomes governed learning and promotion truth"]
    L7["The whole run closes through reconstruction, verdict, idle-safe teardown, and cost accountability"]
    L8["That is the current wired architecture A has surfaced"]
  end

  subgraph OWNERSHIP["4. Deepest thing A proves: truth-boundary ownership"]
    T1["The platform is not treating data moved as enough"]
    T2["Ingress truth stays ingress truth"]
    T3["RTDL decision, action, and lineage truth stays RTDL truth"]
    T4["Case truth stays case-management truth"]
    T5["Label truth stays label truth"]
    T6["Dataset truth stays offline-dataset truth"]
    T7["Model-eval truth stays train-and-eval truth"]
    T8["Active model or policy truth stays registry truth"]
    T9["That is the clearest single sign that the current wired system is architected intentionally rather than accreted service by service"]
    T10["A also proves material existence, not just conceptual design: the platform is seated on explicit managed and runtime surfaces across all major planes, with durable evidence roots and explicit pass gates plus commit evidence for closure"]
  end

  subgraph PROOF["5. Proof-category closure"]
    P1["Across the proof categories, A is now strong"]
    P2["Completeness closes because A covers all major planes: control and ingress, RTDL, case and label, learning and evolution, operations, governance, and meta, and ties them together under one closure map"]
    P3["Existence closes because every major boundary is materially seated"]
    P4["Uniqueness closes because the run and process law insists on one active runtime path per phase or run, explicit active-bundle resolution, explicit append-only ownership, and explicit gates and evidence"]
    P5["Continuity closes because the architecture now reads as one causal chain from source world to runtime to supervision to learning to governed activation to run closure"]
    P6["Safety closes because the whole design is fail-closed on the right things: no future leakage, no silent defaulting, no read without pass, no shadow truth ownership, no phase closure without evidence, and no advancement on unattributed spend"]
  end

  subgraph AMBIG["6. Remaining A ambiguities and Bi boundary"]
    A1["The remaining A ambiguities are narrower than the core claim"]
    A2["The main ones are explanatory: keeping platform run identity distinct from sealed source-world identity"]
    A3["Keeping current wired runtime seating distinct from target or retained runtime posture where those differ"]
    A4["Keeping audit truth, archive truth, replay-reference closure, case truth, label truth, dataset truth, and runtime authority truth separate in the reader-facing story instead of collapsing them into convenience labels"]
    A5["Those are now clarity risks rather than existence risks"]
    A6["Bi remains the place to prove whether these boundaries hold under production pressure, intended envelopes, and harder operational conditions"]
  end

  subgraph VERDICT["7. Honest verdict"]
